review_blob: Black with a thick brown head. Aroma of coffee, chocolate, roast malt, chili, earthy hops. Taste was light sweet with a light bitter finish. Thick oily texture with low carbonation. Really nice beer.
Hazy gold with a thin-medium white head. Aroma of fruit, citrus hops, sweet malt. Sweet with a light bitter finish. Thin oily texture, low-medium carbonation.
beer_name: Rogue Nation Brutal India Pale Ale

review_blob: Golden with a medium white head. Aroma of fruit, citrus hops, caramel malt. Sweet with a medium bitter finish. Oily texture low-medium carbonation. Good beer.
Golden with a thin, white head. Aroma of floral hops, caramel malt. Sweet with a light bitter finish. Thin oily texture, light carbonation. Pretty nice beer.
Hazy golden, with a big frothy white head. Aroma of citrus hops, orange, yeast, straw. Taste was sweet with a light bitter finish. Light oily texture, low carbonation. Good beer.
Black with a medium, quickly diminishing, beige head. Aroma of yeast, roast malt, fruit. Taste is sweet with a bitter finish. Full body, thick oily texture, low carbonation. Nice beer.
beer_name: Gnstaller Bru / Nrke / De Molen B&H; MeGa Schwarzer Bock

review_blob: Decent IPA. Grapefruit, hops etc. Low sweet, bitter finish. Oily texture, low carbonation.
Clear, golden with a medium sized white head. Aroma of fruit, hops. Nie taste, light sweet with a light bitter finish. Good standard pale ale.
Clear red/brown with a medium, quickly-diminishing, beige head. Aroma of nuts, chocolate, caramel malt. Taste is low sweet with a bitter finish. Good.
Clear burnt red with a massive off-whire/beige head. Aroma of citrus, pine, caramel. Taste is light sweet with a pleasing, well-balanced bitter finish. Great beer.
Hazy red/brown with a massive off-white head. Aroma of citrus, yeast, straw, nutty, caramel malt. Taste is light sweet, light sour finish. Light oily texture, high carbonation. Refreshing, tasty..
Hazy golden with a thin/medium white head. Aroma is hoppy, citrus, pine. Taste is light sweet with a bitter finish. Thin oily texture, a little watery, low carbonation. OK.
Murky gold/brown with a thin white head. Aroma of citrus, hops, wheat. Taste is sweet with a light bitter finish. Thin oily texture, medium carbonation. Nice.
Cloudy, golden with a big white head. Aroma of peach, citrus, flora hops. Taste is sweet with a bitter finish, really well balanced. Oily texture, medium carbonation, silky. Really nice beer.

Clear, golden with a small-medium white head. Aroma of floral hops, malt, apple. Very sweet with a bitter finish. Thin, oily texture, low carbonation. Not sure if it works for me, a touch too sweet...

Clear golden with a medium white head. Aroma of citrus, hops, straw, caramel malt. Taste is light sweet with a big bitter finish (a little overpowering perhaps). Oily texture, low carbonation. Not the best balanced beer ever...
Black with a massive beige head. Aroma of smoke, roast malt, yeast. Taste is light sweet with a sour and bitter finish. Really nice.
Straw coloured, with a foamy white head. Hops, light malt. Light oily texture, medium carbonation, crisp, dry finish. Refreshing. Good beer.
Murky golen/brown with a thing white head. Full, floral, citrus, skunky hops, pine, malt. Sweet with a well balanced, bitter finish. Texture is oily, medium carbonation. Really tasty beer.
beer_name: The Kernel India Pale Ale Amarillo Rakau

review_blob: Clear red/amber with a medium off-white head. Citrus, floral hops, sweet malt. Sweet with a bitter finish. Oily texture, low carbonation. Really nice.
Clear red, with a thin beige head. Aroma of malt, chocolate, earthy hops, whisky. Taste is sweet, caramel, light bitter finish, rich. Thick oily texture, low carbonation, full bodied. Pretty good.
Very malty for the style. Sweet, caramel malt, bitter finish. Thick oily texture, low-med carbonation. Ok, not one of mikkellers best though.
Clear, golden, medium white head. Citrus hops, malt. Sweet with a bitter finish. Oily texture, low carbonation. Good beer, refreshing.
Clear, golden, big white head. Aroma of pine, floral hops, malt. Taste was light sweet, strong bitter finish. Oily texture, crisp. Refreshing. Good beer.
Clear, red small/med off-white head. Caramel malt, floral hops. Light sweet, bitter finish. Thin, oily texture, low carbonation. Good.

Golden with a thin/medium, quickly dissipating, white head. Aroma of hops, spices, fruit, herbs. Sweet with a bitter and very tart finish, a lot going on on the tongue! Oily texture, low/med carbonation. Good beer.
Hazy golden with a massive foamy white head. Aroma of floral hops, sherbet, spices. Taste is sweet with a bitter finish. Oily texture, silky, low carbonation. Good.
Light straw coloured with a thin/medium white head. Aroma of herbs, floral hops, sherbet, spices. Taste is sweet with light sour finish. Thin oily texture, medium/high carbonation.
Murky red/brown, very thin, very quickly dissipating, off white head. Aroma of fruit, toffee, brandy, caramel malt. Sweet taste, light sour and light bitter finish.

Hazy red/brown with a thin off-white head. Light aroma of citrus/floral hops, grapefruit, caramel malt. Taste is light sweet with a really nice, well balanced bitter finish. Thick oily texture, low carbonation. Good beer.

Brown/amber with a big foamy off white head. Aroma of yeast, citrus, lemon, sweet malt. Taste light sweet with a bitter finish. Thick oily texture, light/med carbonation. Really tasty, though I maybe poured it a bit too enthusiastically as there is quite a bit if stuff floating in it.

Black with thick tan head. Aroma of chocolate, coffee, roast malt, bread, yeast. Taste is light sweet, really well balanced, bitter finish. Full body, thick oily texture, low/medium carbonation. Very good beer.

Golden, opaque, medium/large foamy white head. Aroma of yeast, wheat, citrus, floral hops. Taste sweet with a really well balanced, light sour and light bitter finish. Smooth, thick oily texture, low/medium carbonation. Really nice hefeweizen. Great beer.
Black with no head. Aroma of roast malt, smoke, chocolate, coffee, dark fruit. Taste is sweet with well balanced, bitter finish. Thick oily texture, low carbonation. Good beer.
beer_name: Evil Twin Christmas Eve at a New York City Hotel Room (2011-)

review_blob: Black with a massive beige head. Aroma of chocolate, roast malt, wood, smoke, bourbon, yeast. Taste is light sweet, really well balanced light sour and bitter finish. Oily texture , medium/high carbonation. Really good beer.

Black with a thin tan head. Aroma of roast malt, coffee, chocolate, milk, oats, a little smoke. Taste is sweet with a light bitter finish. Texture is thin/medium oily,low/medium carbonation. Really nice.

Clear golden/amber with a thin white head. Aroma is orange, citrus hops, caramel malt. Taste is light sweet with a medium/heavy bitter finish. Texture is thin, oily, medium carbonation. Good, expect a bit more from Tool though.
Hazy golden, with a medium white head. Fruity aroma, plenty of citrus hops, orange, peach. Taste is sweet with a light bitter finish. Oily texture, low carbonation. Very nice.

Hazy golden with a thin/medium white head. Strong citrus aroma, plenty of orange and lemon, fruit, hops, caramel malt. Taste is sweet, with a well balanced bitter finish. Silky, oily texture, low carbonation. Good beer.

Clear golden with a medium, foamy white head. Armoma is strong lemon, citrus, the thyme is relatively subtle, sherbet. Taste is very sweet with a tart, sour finish. Think oily texture, medium carbonation. Nice beer, maybe a bit too much like a lemonade.

Black with a massive beige head. Aroma of smoke, roasted malt, coffee, chocolate, yeast. Taste is light sweet, with a sour and bitter finish. Thin oily texture, medium carbonation, perhaps overcarbonated for the style. Good beer.

Slightly hazy, golden with a big foamy white head. Aroma is very citrussy, plenty of lemon, a little orange, wheat. Taste is light sweet with a really well balanced, light bitter finish. Light oily texture, low/med carbonation. Very refreshing, great beer for the summer.

Murky yellow/brown with a thin, quickly dissipating white head. Aroma of malt, fruit, hops. Taste is sweet, with a light sour and bitter finish. Thin oily texture, low/med carbonation. OK, nothing special.
beer_name: Bad Seed South Pacific Pale Ale

review_blob: Golden/amber with a large foamy, but quickly diminishing, white head. Aroma of yeast, fruit, spices, ginger, citrus, lemon, hops. Taste is sweet with a bitter finish, really well balanced. Thin oily texture, medium carbonation. Tasty beer, really refreshing.

Golden/amber with a medium/large offwhite head. Fruity, citrus aroma, orange, grapefruit, floral hops. Taste is sweet, really well balanced, nice bitter finish. Oily texture, low carbonation. Really nice, very refreshing IPA. Excellent.
Black with a thick beige head. Aroma of burnt, roast malt, smoke, coffee, earthy hops. Taste is light sweet with a long bitter finish. Thin/medium oily texture, with low carbonation. Good.

Black with a massive frothy light brown/beige head. Aroma of cream, roast malt, smoke, chocolate, coffee, earthy hops. Taste is sweet with a lovely, well balanced bitter finish. Thick oily texture, low carbonation. Really, really good beer.

Cloudy gold/amber with a big white head. Aroma of fruit, citrus, lemon hops. Taste is sweet malt, with a strong tangy, sour and light bitter finish, well balanced. Texture is oily, medium carbonation, crisp & refreshing. Really good beer.

Black with a massive beige head. Aroma of wood, grape, bourbon, earthy hops, roast malt, chocolate. Taste is light sweet with a sour and bitter finish, well balanced. Thick oily texture, medium/low carbonation. Good beer.
Golden with a big white head. Fruity aroma, citrus, orange, fresh floral hops. Taste is sweet with a well balanced, big bitter finish. Oily texture, low/medium carbonation. Really nice beer.
